IDE0250 keeps track of structs that can be marked `readonly`. This leads to issues when any of its fields is a `ref struct`.
Take the following snippet:

``` C#
public ref struct Data(ReadOnlySpan<char> input, Span<char> buffer)
{
    private readonly ReadOnlySpan<char> Input = input;
    private readonly Span<char> Buffer = buffer;
}
```

By excluding structs that have `ref struct` properties, this False Positive will not longer be reported.

Previously, this rule has been adjusted to ignore structs containing events: #69994
